That goals shifted the momentum of the match and Kagawa put Japan in front when he retained his balance to sweep a right-footed shot past Costa Rica goalkeeper Keilor Navas with 10 minutes left.

Kakitani, on as a substitute, made sure of the win in stoppage time at the Raymond James Stadium, home of the NFL side Tampa Bay Buccaneers.

Japan coach Alberto Zaccheroni will be pleased with the manner of the win and his team's smart and positive passing style throughout the match but, aside from their goal, Costa Rica rarely threatened their opponent's goal.

